                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14409324" author="djackman" created="Thu, 10 Nov 2005 12:40:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The attached patch fixes this problem.  Instead of keeping the list of merged plugins for parent and child in a map, it keeps the list in a List.  (It still uses the maps to make sure plugins are only executed once if mentioned in both parent and child.)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14409438" author="djackman" created="Thu, 10 Nov 2005 13:32:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;After further inspection, I realized that the ModelUtils.mergePluginDefinitions method had the same problem.  The second attached patch fixes the problem there as well.  This patch also adds unit tests to cover these changes.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14409464" author="jdcasey" created="Thu, 17 Nov 2005 14:48:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Applied. Thanks, David.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
